# Debian vs Red Hat Command Differences for LFCS

## ğŸŒ Package Management
- Debian: apt update / apt upgrade / apt install pkg / apt remove pkg
- RedHat: yum update / yum install pkg / yum remove pkg OR dnf for newer versions

## ğŸ”§ Service Management
- Same for both (systemd):
   systemctl start|stop|restart|enable|disable|status service_name
  
## ğŸ“ Config File Paths
- Debian: /etc/network/interfaces (older), netplan configs in /etc/netplan/
- RedHat: /etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/ifcfg-<interface>

## ğŸŒ Networking - Restart Network
- Debian: systemctl restart networking
- RedHat: systemctl restart network

## ğŸŒ Check IP / Interfaces
- Same for both: ip addr OR ip a

## ğŸ” SELinux vs AppArmor
- Debian: AppArmor (default)
- RedHat: SELinux (default)  
  getenforce / setenforce to manage SELinux (RedHat only)

## ğŸ”§ Firewall
- Debian: ufw enable / ufw allow 22 / ufw status
- RedHat: 
   firewall-cmd --add-port=22/tcp --permanent
  firewall-cmd --reload
  
## ğŸ—‚ï¸ Package File Search
- Debian: dpkg -L pkg_name
- RedHat: rpm -ql pkg_name

## ğŸ” Find Package Providing File
- Debian: apt-file search filename
- RedHat: yum provides filename OR dnf provides filename

## ğŸ‘¤ User & Group Management
- Same for both: useradd, passwd, usermod, groupadd, groups

## ğŸ“‚ Software Repo Config
- Debian: /etc/apt/sources.list
- RedHat: /etc/yum.repos.d/

## ğŸ§¹ Clean Package Cache
- Debian: apt clean OR apt autoremove
- RedHat: yum clean all

## ğŸ“¦ Check Installed Packages
- Debian: dpkg -l
- RedHat: rpm -qa

## ğŸ§¾ Package Info
- Debian: apt show pkg_name
- RedHat: yum info pkg_name OR rpm -qi pkg_name

## ğŸ’» Hostname Management
- Same for both: hostnamectl set-hostname newname

## ğŸ—„ï¸ Log Files
- Debian: /var/log/syslog, /var/log/auth.log
- RedHat: /var/log/messages, /var/log/secure

## ğŸ“œ Default Shell Config Files
- Debian: /etc/bash.bashrc
- RedHat: /etc/bashrc

## ğŸ“¡ Network Tools (Install)
- Debian: apt install net-tools
- RedHat: yum install net-tools

## ğŸŒ Default Web Root (Apache)
- Both: /var/www/html (same path, config files may differ)

## âš™ï¸ Time Sync
- Debian: timedatectl set-ntp true
- RedHat: chronyd service or timedatectl

## ğŸ§° Common Package Names
- Debian: apache2, php, build-essential
- RedHat: httpd, php, gcc, make, rpm-build